pcoming introduction of a new and consolidated brand in autumn 2017, I will have accomplished my mission at Tele Columbus to make the company fit for the future", states the native Belgian Ronny Verhelst. "I would like to thank all my colleagues at Tele Columbus for their fantastic commitment as well as all our partners for the excellent cooperation over the past seven years. At the same time, I would like to ask for their understanding regarding my decision to relocate my focal point of life to my home in Belgium." "It is almost impossible to adequately value Ronny's achievements. With his vast experience, his strategic skillset, his strong execution capability and his drive, he successfully managed to turn the company around", comments Frank Donck, chairman of the supervisory board of Tele Columbus AG. "In the name of the entire supervisory board I would like to thank Ronny for his achievements and we wish him all the best for his professional and private future. At the same time, we are very happy to have won with Timm Degenhardt a high-qualified and experienced successor. With a strong commercial background and customer focus, Timm is also truly familiar with the telecommunications and infrastructure market and, over the past couple of years, actively shaped the digitalisation of the media industry in several key positions. Together with him, we would like to continue the growth path for Tele Columbus." German Timm Degenhardt is joining from the Swiss telecommunications provider Sunrise, most recently as Chief Consumer Officer and member of the management board with responsibility for the entire consumer business. Prior to this, he was Chief Marketing Officer and Chief Commercial Officer at Sunrise since 2013 and with his drive for both customer orientation and digitalisation laid foundations for the successful Sunrise IPO. Previously, Timm Degenhardt was CEO at aizo Group, a smart home applications company, since 2010 and Senior Vice President Marketing & Sales at E.ON AG since 2007. This was preceded by several senior leadership positions at American Express and at the telecommunications provider Orange, where he was a member of the management board and Vice President for Marketing and Product Development since 2004. Timm Degenhardt holds a Master of Science in Marketing Management from Nottingham Business School and a degree level diploma in Marketing from the Chartered Institute of Marketing in London. "I am very excited to commence my new role, because I am truly convinced that the new digital applications, the growing demand for media content and the increasing mobile usage will offer great opportunities for a high performance broadband internet and entertainment provider such as Tele Columbus", states Timm Degenhardt, who will join the company's management effectively 14 August 2017. "The German market has to catch up a lot in international comparisons when it comes to innovation and adaption of new tech and media trends. In my opinion, a nation-wide yet also locally-footed provider like Tele Columbus offers excellent opportunities to tap that potential." ________________  About Tele Columbus  The SDAX listed Tele Columbus Group is one of Germany's largest cable network operators. Via its origins - individual regional cable network operators that were merged into Tele Columbus - the company dates back to 1972. Today, about 3.6 million connected households in Germany are served by Tele Columbus, primacom, pepcom, Deutsche Telekabel, Martens und KMS with TV signals and, increasingly, digital broadcast packages, Internet and voice connections provided via high-performance broadband cable. As a national provider with a regional focus and a partner of the housing industry, the Group is present throughout its core markets Berlin, Brandenburg, Saxony, Saxony-Anhalt and Thuringia as well as in numerous key regions in western Germany. In tune with current demand trends, the company is upgrading its networks in a hybrid fibre-optic infrastructure for superfast Internet connections of up to several hundred megabits per second with the state-of-the-art Internet transmission standard DOCSIS 3.0. The broadband cable caters to the entire range of innovative media applications from analogous, digital and high-definition TV to high-speed Internet and voice connections to telemetry services, tenant portals and interactive services. Beyond merely transmitting signals, Tele Columbus uses its own product platform in order to actively increase the programme offering and to develop additional services. Via its company HL komm, Tele Columbus also delivers powerful connections and network services to business customers.  Contact:   Hannes Lindhuber  Director Communications  Phone +49 (30) 3388 4170  Fax +49 (30) 3388 9 1999  presse@telecolumbus.de  www.telecolumbus.com     24.07.2017 Dissemination of a Corporate News, transmitted by DGAP - a service of EQS Group AG.The issuer is solely responsible for the content of this announcement.The DGAP Distribution Services include Regulatory Announcements, Financial/Corporate News and Press Releases. Archive at www.dgap.de     Language: English   Company: Tele Columbus AG    Kaiserin-Augusta-Allee 108    10553 Berlin    Germany   Phone: +49 (0)30 3388 4177   Fax: +49 (0)30 3388 9 1999   E-mail: Hannes.Lindhuber@telecolumbus.de   Internet: www.telecolumbus.de   ISIN: DE000TCAG172   WKN: TCAG17    Indices: SDAX   Listed: Regulated Market in Frankfurt (Prime Standard); Regulated Unofficial Market in Berlin, Dusseldorf, Hamburg, Munich, Stuttgart, Tradegate Exchange        End of News DGAP News Service show thisMoreReblogShareTweetShareRecently ViewedYour list is empty.What to read nextPound slumps after Bank of England updateAFPStart Living The Millionaire LifestyleTorOptionSponsoredSix reasons to say no to a smart meterThe TelegraphCouple hit with £10,000 worth of fines for parking outside their luxury flatYahoo Finance UKCo-op to target cashpoint theft by spray